x4freetext: The Radial Ridge AVF cyclotron
The overall energy resolution obtained during the
majority of these measurements was between 65 keV FWHM
and 100 keV FWHM.
Silicon surface barrier detectors were placed at
five equal-spaced positions on each of the two moveable
arms of the scattering chamber. With this system
measurements could be made at up to ten different
angles simultaneously. The solid angles subtended by
the ten detectors at the target, and also their angles
of acceptance, where all identical at 0.900*10** -4 sr
and + - 0.300 degr. respectively. The detectors were
cooled to -10 degr. by cold ethanol circulated through
the plates on which they were mounted. During the
initial experiment in the series the solid angles and
angles of acceptance of all ten detector  systems were
checked and found to be identical to within 1%. Two
fixed angle monitor detectors were placed at + - 22.5
degr. scattering angle but raised 20 degr. in azimuth
so that they had a clear view of the target over the
main detector assemblies on the two
moveable arms.
